King Felipe VI of Spain welcomed President Biden and his delegation to Madrid for the NATO Summit. The two leaders emphasized the deep historical and cultural ties between Spain and the United States, as well as their shared values and principles. They discussed the importance of unity among Allied countries in defending freedom and democratic values. President Biden expressed gratitude for Spain's support, both in Europe and in regions like North Africa and Latin America. He highlighted the significance of the partnership between their countries in shaping the future and emphasized the need for democracies to stay united in the face of challenges from autocracies.